description: Numbers n whose prime factors are 3 and 5.
comments: n such that phi(n)=(8/15)*n. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Apr 19 2002A143201(a(n))=3; subsequence of A143202; a(n)=15*A003593(n). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
prog: (Haskell)import Data.Set (singleton, deleteFindMin, insert)a033849 n = a033849_list !! (n-1)a033849_list = f (singleton (3*5)) where   f s = m : f (insert (3*m) $ insert (5*m) s') where     (m,s') = deleteFindMin s-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011
